article.headline: Brown 59, Army 57
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. (AP) -- Scott Friske's tip-in with less than a second left gave Brown a 59-57 win over Army Saturday. Friske led the Bears (3-8) with 24 points and Damon Huffman added 14. Matt Bell led the Black Knights (4-7) with 20 points, while Colin Harris had 17. Bell tied the game on a short jumper in the lane with eight seconds remaining. An Army turnover gave Brown possession in the closing seconds. The Bears connected on 5-of-11 3-pointers in the first half to build a 23-20 halftime lead. They took their biggest lead of the game at 51-44 with six minutes to play. An 11-4 spurt by the Black Knights tied the game at 55 with 1:39 left.
